The N1 near Bela-Bela in Limpopo was reopened late Sunday night. JOHANNESBURG - The N1 near Bela-Bela in Limpopo was reopened late Sunday night after a fuel tanker caught alight. Preliminary reports suggest that a burst tyre could have sparked the fire. WATCH: N1 North to Bela Bela closed after fire Authorities are investigating the cause of the accident. The driver escaped unharmed. In a separate incident, on the same stretch of road, one person was killed in a crash. Police are investigating a case of culpable homicide.